# Netlify security headers for atlasaileads.com
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NOTE: this file only covers STATIC files Netlify serves directly (e.g. the
# /demos/*.html bundles). Next.js-rendered pages (/, /services, ...) are served
# by the Next runtime and do NOT read this file — those are covered by an
# identical `securityHeaders` list in next.config.ts `headers()`. Keep both in
# sync. Both are required for full coverage on Netlify + Next.js.
#
# These harden browser security WITHOUT changing site design, copy, forms,
# demos, or behavior. The Content-Security-Policy is REPORT-ONLY: it observes
# and logs to the browser console but blocks NOTHING, so it cannot break the
# demos, videos, or fonts. Flip it to an enforced `Content-Security-Policy`
# header only after reviewing that the console shows no legitimate violations.
#
# X-Frame-Options is SAMEORIGIN (not DENY) on purpose: the site iframes its
# own same-origin /demos/*.html and video pages, which SAMEORIGIN still allows.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

/*
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000
  Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'self'; frame-src 'self'; form-action 'self' mailto:; img-src 'self' data: blob:; media-src 'self' blob:; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com data:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval' blob:; worker-src 'self' blob:; connect-src 'self' blob:
